label.value: Personalized Cancer Vaccine RO7198457
Prostate Cancer by AJCC v8 Stage

value.value: A term that refers to the staging of prostate cancer according to the American Joint Committee on Cancer, 8th edition. This staging system applies to adenocarcinomas and squamous cell carcinomas of the prostate gland. It does not apply to sarcomas, urothelial cell carcinomas, and urothelial carcinoma of bladder involving prostate. (from AJCC 8th Ed.)

label.value: Stage I Prostate Cancer AJCC v8

value.value: Stage I includes: (cT1a-c, cT2a, N0, M0, PSA less than 10, Grade Group 1); (pT2, N0, M0, PSA less than 10, Grade Group 1). cT1a: Prostate cancer in which the tumor is an incidental histologic finding in 5% or less of tissue resected. cT1b: Prostate cancer in which the tumor is an incidental histologic finding in more than 5% of tissue resected. cT1c: Prostate cancer in which the tumor is identified by needle biopsy found in one or both sides, but not palpable. cT2a: Prostate cancer in which the tumor involves one-half of one side or less. pT2: Prostate cancer which is organ confined. N0: Prostate cancer with no positive regional nodes. M0: Prostate cancer without evidence of distant metastasis. Grade Group 1: Gleason Score 6 or less, Gleason Pattern 3 or less+3. (AJCC 8th ed.)

label.value: Stage II Prostate Cancer AJCC v8

value.value: Stage II includes: IIA: (cT1a-c, cT2a, N0, M0, PSA equal or more than 10 and less than 20, Grade Group 1); (cT2b-c, N0, M0, PSA less than 20, Grade Group 1); IIB: T1-2, N0, M0, PSA less than 20, Grade Group 2; IIC: (T1-2, N0, M0, PSA less than 20, Grade Group 3); (T1-2, N0, M0, PSA less than 20, Grade Group 4). cT1a: Prostate cancer in which the tumor is an incidental histologic finding in 5% or less of tissue resected. cT1b: Prostate cancer in which the tumor is an incidental histologic finding in more than 5% of tissue resected. cT1c: Prostate cancer in which the tumor is identified by needle biopsy found in one or both sides, but not palpable. cT2a: Prostate cancer in which the tumor involves one-half of one side or less. cT2b: Prostate cancer in which the tumor involves more than one-half of one side but not both sides. cT2c: Prostate cancer in which the tumor involves both sides. T1: Prostate cancer with clinically inapparent tumor that is not palpable. T2: Prostate cancer in which the tumor is palpable and confined within the prostate. N0: Prostate cancer with no positive regional nodes. M0: Prostate cancer without evidence of distant metastasis. Grade Group 1: Gleason Score 6 or less, Gleason Pattern 3 or less+3. Grade Group 2: Gleason Score 7, Gleason Pattern 3+4. Grade Group 3: Gleason Score 7, Gleason Pattern 4+3. Grade Group 4: Gleason Score 8, Gleason Pattern 4+4. (AJCC 8th ed.)

label.value: Stage IIA Prostate Cancer AJCC v8

value.value: Stage IIA includes: (cT1a-c, cT2a, N0, M0, PSA equal or more than 10 and less than 20, Grade Group 1); (cT2b-c, N0, M0, PSA less than 20, Grade Group 1). cT1a: Prostate cancer in which the tumor is an incidental histologic finding in 5% or less of tissue resected. cT1b: Prostate cancer in which the tumor is an incidental histologic finding in more than 5% of tissue resected. cT1c: Prostate cancer in which the tumor is identified by needle biopsy found in one or both sides, but not palpable. cT2a: Prostate cancer in which the tumor involves one-half of one side or less. cT2b: Prostate cancer in which the tumor involves more than one-half of one side but not both sides. cT2c: Prostate cancer in which the tumor involves both sides. label.value: MSANTD1 Gene

value.value: This gene may be involved in both DNA binding and chromatin remodeling.

label.value: Subviral Satellite

value.value: A subviral agent composed of nucleic acid that depends on the co-infection of a host cell with a helper virus for its replication.

label.value: MSANTD1 wt Allele

value.value: Human MSANTD1 wild-type allele is located in the vicinity of 4p16.3 and is approximately 3 kb in length. This allele, which encodes Myb/SANT-like DNA-binding domain-containing protein 1, may play a role in chromatin remodeling.

label.value: Myb/SANT-Like DNA-Binding Domain-Containing Protein 1

value.value: Myb/SANT-like DNA-binding domain-containing protein 1 (278 aa, ~32 kDa) is encoded by the human MSANTD1 gene. This protein may be involved in binding to both histones and DNA.

label.value: CELSR2 Gene

value.value: This gene plays a role in cell-cell signaling during the development of the nervous system.

label.value: CELSR2 wt Allele

value.value: Human CELSR2 wild-type allele is located in the vicinity of 1p13.3 and is approximately 26 kb in length. This allele, which encodes cadherin EGF LAG seven-pass G-type receptor 2 protein, is involved in cell-cell signaling.

label.value: Cadherin EGF LAG Seven-Pass G-Type Receptor 2

value.value: Cadherin EGF LAG seven-pass G-type receptor 2 (2923 aa, ~317 kDa) is encoded by the human CELSR2 gene. This protein plays a role in Wnt signaling and neural development.
